<h2>Interurban moving</h2>
<p>The cost of an inter-city move depends on the weight of the load and the distance from the point of origin to the point of destination. Atlas experts will provide you with an accurate estimate allowing you to properly budget for your move.</p>
<p>An Atlas moving consultant will come to your home to take inventory item by item of everything you will be moving. If you store items away from home, be sure to keep a detailed list.</p>
<p>Your Grewal moving consultant will explain each step of the moving process to you. He will also introduce you to the various programs designed to protect your goods during transport or storage, and he will work with you to determine the service options, as well as the moving schedule including packing, loading and delivery.</p>
<p>Your consultant will then prepare an estimate - or price proposal - for your inter-city move. This estimate will include the costs of all moving services requested, whether it be transportation, packaging, storage or replacement cost protection.</p>
<p>The exact cost of your inter-city move will be calculated when the truck is weighed after it has been loaded. Most Grewal moving consultants guarantee that the difference between the actual weight and the estimated weight will not exceed 10%, as long as you do not add items to be moved after the inventory will be taken at your home.</p>
<h3>payment methods</h3>
